uation-plan.md:14:4. [Phase 3: Real Workload Testing (Day 3-5)](#4-phase-3-real-workload-testing-day-3-5)\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:15:5. [Phase 4: Concurrent Load Testing (Day 5-6)](#5-phase-4-concurrent-load-testing-day-5-6)\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:26:### 1.1 Verify Dual-Ollama Topology\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:37:# Verify NUMA pinning — each ollama-runner should be bound to its socket\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:73:# Verify instance 1 can see them:\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:217:You are a software development orchestrator. Below is a Product Requirements Document (PRD) for a new feature. Decompose it into discrete work items suitable for a coding agent working in git worktrees.\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:342:# Verify token count estimate (rough: 1 token ~ 4 chars)\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:348:Test every candidate model on both NUMA sockets with all three prompt lengths. This is the most time-consuming sub-step — expect 4-8 hours for the full matrix.\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:372:      echo \\\\\\\">>> Testing $model on port $port with $prompt\\\\\\\"\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:392:    echo \\\\\\\">>> Testing $model on port 11434 with $prompt\\\\\\\"\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:522:### 3.1 Test Harness Setup\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:544:### 3.2 Test: Single Tool Call — Orchestrator Task Classification\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:587:### 3.3 Test: Multi-Step Tool Chaining — Network Ops API Sequence\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:666:### 3.4 Test: Structured JSON Output — Reviewer Scoring\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:668:Prompt the model to produce a structured code review. Test with `\\\\\\\"format\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"json\\\\\\\"` in the API call.\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:685:### 3.5 Test: Error Recovery — Tool Returns an Error\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:692:### 3.6 Test: Coding Agent — Bug Fix from Error Trace\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:722:| Test | Criteria | Score |\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:743:## 4. Phase 3: Real Workload Testing (Day 3-5)\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:770:### 4.2 PromptClaw Workload: Code Implementation\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:818:| Model | PRD Decomposition | Code Implementation | Code Review | FortiGate Parsing | Topology Diagram | Average |\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:827:## 5. Phase 4: Concurrent Load Testing (Day 5-6)\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:829:**Goal:** Verify that the selected models work when running simultaneously, as they will in production.\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:843:### 5.4 OLLAMA_NUM_PARALLEL Stress Test\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:978:| KV cache at 32K context blows RAM budget | Low | High | Test at target context lengths; reduce context if needed |\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:979:| OLLAMA_NUM_PARALLEL causes thrashing | Low | Medium | Test in Phase 4; fall back to NUM_PARALLEL=1 |\\\\n+docs/r750-model-evaluation-plan.md:981:| Ollama version incompatibility with newer architectures | Low | High | Test on eval day; pin Ollama version that works |\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-presence-cadence-spec.md:825:## Implementation Phases\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-presence-cadence-spec.md:827:Implementation should proceed in CPU-safe layers. The live box is already\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-presence-cadence-spec.md:942:## Test Plan\\\\n+docs/cypherclaw-presence-cadence-spec.md:944:Implementation should be test-first.\\\\n+sdp/templates/gemini/fix_verify.md:21:    *   If the feedback is purely about style or formatting (`PASS WITH NOTES`), do not just blindly accept it. Document the disagreement in `ESCALATIONS.md` and proceed.\\\\n+sdp/templates/gemini/fix_verify.md:22:3.  **Verify**: Run all tests and quality checks.\\\\n+docs/r750-application-deployment-plan.md:1:# PromptClaw Application D