sdp/verification/t-014@20260427t001208z-verify.md:11:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-27T17:55:04.459Z","role":"user","content":"# Verification: Task T-014@20260427T001208Z\n\n**Task:** Implement `_should_queue_now(mode, mood, learning)` heuristic based on cycle rate and homogeneity flags.\n**Tier:** T1\n\nYou are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- Returns True when ALL of: (a) at least 30 minutes since last enqueued generation, (b) the existing sampler antipattern detectors don't currently report `sampler_dominating`, (c) the daily budget has > $0.50 remaining<br/>- Returns True 100% of the time when no generation has ever been enqueued (cold start)<br/>- Returns False if mode is `working_ambience` and current piece's arc_payoff < 0.4 (don't generate during quiet work)<br/>- Tests with synthetic state cover each branch\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n1. **Review recent commits:**\n   ```bash\n   git log --oneline -5\n   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\n   ```\n\n2. **Review code changes:**\n   ```bash\n   git diff HEAD~3\n   ```\n\n4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\n\n5. **Run the test suite:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\n   ```\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\nEvaluate the work against these five dimensions:\n\n1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\n2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\n3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\n4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\n5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\n\n## Output\n\nWrite your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\n`sdp/verification/t-014@20260427t001208z-verify.md`\nDo not use a different filename or directory.\n\nUse this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Report — T-014@20260427T001208Z\n\n**Verif