my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/metrics.py:78:    # For testing and decoupling, if score is a dict with raw pre-extracted
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:16:- Bart Hopkin, *Musical Instrument Design* — resonance, harmonics, **every material has a latent voice**
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:17:- Rimsky-Korsakov, *Principles of Orchestration* — voice blending, **the orchestra as a single organism**
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:31:20 Hz       → the lowest audible pitch / a fast tremolo
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:32:4 Hz        → a slow tremolo / a fast rhythmic pulse
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:57:At control rate (0.1-20Hz), an Oscillator modulates other Oscillators (tremolo, vibrato, filter sweep).
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:62:Modulation is how Oscillators interact. An LFO modulating pitch = vibrato. A sensor reading modulating density = reactive texture. A narrative arc position modulating harmonic complexity = story-driven music. It's all the same operation: one Oscillator changing another's parameters.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:68:├── modulates → harmonic_complexity, motif_development, voice_count
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:75:│   │   │   ├── ControlOscillator (0.1-20Hz) — vibrato, tremolo, filter modulation
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:86:├── TheraminiOscillator — derived from Theramini MIDI CC#20, modulates lead voice
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:94:Every material has a latent voice. The contact mics reveal it. Before generating any synthetic sound, the system should:
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:98:3. **Characterize** — build a spectral fingerprint of the house's current voice
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:101:The house voice changes with conditions. The furnace hums at one frequency. Rain creates broadband noise with rhythmic density. Wind creates low-frequency pressure oscillation. Footsteps create transient impulses. Each of these is material speaking, and CypherClaw should speak back in the same harmonic language.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:143:- Evening → Night: Eb major → C minor (expansion becoming depth)
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:175:**Orchestration Principle 1: Unified Will.** At any moment, the organism has one emotional intention. Every voice serves that intention. If the intention is "gentle contemplation," no voice should be agitated.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:177:**Orchestration Principle 2: Foreground/Background.** At most 1-2 voices are in the foreground (melody, lead). The rest are background (drone, texture, pulse). The foreground rotates based on which organism character is most active.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:179:**Orchestration Principle 3: Doubling.** When two voices play the same line in different registers, the sound gains body without gaining complexity. Window (low) and Garden Eye (high) doubling at the octave creates a full sound with only one melodic idea.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:181:**Orchestration Principle 4: Silence as Voice.** The rest is an instrument. When a voice drops out, the absence is heard. Strategic silence creates space for the listener's imagination. (Eco: the reader co-creates meaning in the gaps.)
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:183:**Orchestration Principle 5: Tutti and Solo.** Tutti (everyone playing) should be rare — reserved for arc climax moments. Most of the time, 2-4 voices are enough. Solo (one voice alone) should happen at least once per section — a moment of nakedness.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:209:Each layer of attention is rewarded. The surface is pleasant. The depths are rich. This is Eco's "open work" — the system doesn't tell you what to feel, it provides the conditions for feeling.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:226:- The harmonic complexity determines which intervals respond to the house's voice
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:227:- The house's voice is what the sensors are hearing
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:268:├── voice.py            # Voice — organism character mapped to register/timbre/role
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:293:    ├── test_voice.py
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:326:Implement `voice.py` and `orchestrator.py`. Each organism character maps to a Voice with register boundaries, timbre family, harmonic role, source type, and activity threshold. The Orchestrator enforces Rimsky-Korsakov principles: unified will (one emotional intention), foreground/background (max 2 voices lead), doubling at octave for warmth, silence as voice (strategic dropouts), tutti reserved for arc climax. Special handling for Theramini: detect human gesture via MIDI CC#20 activity, switch to accompaniment mode (leave space, don't double, respond after). Write tests verifying register constraints, balance rules, silence timing, and accompaniment mode.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:329:Implement `phrase.py`. Generate musical phrases with melodic contour (from harmony.py), rhythmic contour (from rhythm.py), and dynamic contour. Phrase duration follows breathing lengths (4, 8, 12, 16 beats at current tempo). Call-and-response between voices. Variation rules: repetition, transposition, inversion, augmentation, fragmentation, retrograde. Each variation is a modulation of the original phrase's Oscillator parameters. Write tests verifying phrase structure, variation correctness, and breathing.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:338:Implement `arc_music.py`. An Oscillator at arc frequency (~0.0000005 Hz for 25-day cycle). Modulates: harmonic complexity range, voice count range, motif development stage, tutti/solo ratio. At position 0.0: narrow harmonic range, 1-2 voices, motif stated simply. At 0.5: wide range, 4-5 voices, motifs fragmented and layered. At 0.75: climax — full range, tutti moments, all motifs in play. At 1.0: resolution — narrow range, new tonal center, seed motif for next cycle. Reads arc position from narrative world state (same arc as B&P stories). Write tests verifying complexity curves at multiple positions.
my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:344:Implement `engine.py`. The tree of Oscillators from arc root to sample leaves. Main loop: read sensors → update organism moods → update arc position → evaluate section stability → generate phrases for active voices → render Oscillator tree to audio buffer → output to ALSA playback channels. The engine IS the recursive pattern — one loop tick evaluates every Oscillator at its appropriate rate. Integrates all components. Runs as daemon within embodiment service, replacing current `ambient_engine.py`. Graceful startup (fade in over 30 seconds) and shutdown (fade out over 10 seconds). Write integration tests verifying end-to-end audio output.
